{"questionId":"17125","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">In a classical model of the singly-ionized helium atom, a single electron orbits the nucleus in a circular orbit of radius <em>r</em>.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/6616348d2ee9df8cf2261a18502b031373cbb5d9.png\" width=\"249\" height=\"248\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Show that the speed <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math></em> of the electron with mass <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math></em>, is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>e</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">equating centripetal to electrical force&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>e</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math> to get result ✔</span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17125","referenceCode":"19N.2.HL.TZ0.8a(i)","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that the speed v of the electron with mass m, is given by v=2ke2mr.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","10.2 – Fields at work","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}